{"parse":{"title":"Asa'pili","pageid":14716469,"revid":782522606,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Asa'pili</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Constructed_language\" title=\"Constructed language\">constructed language</a> created by the pseudonymous author <a href=\"/wiki/P.M._(author)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"P.M. (author)\">P.M.</a> in his book <a href=\"/wiki/Bolo%27bolo\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bolo&#39;bolo\">Bolo'bolo</a>. On the one hand, it is an <a href=\"/wiki/Artistic_language\" title=\"Artistic language\">artistic language</a>, intended to explain his concepts for a sustainable future in an original way. On the other hand, it is a neutral <a href=\"/wiki/International_auxiliary_language\" title=\"International auxiliary language\">auxiliary language</a> intended for use in the quasi-utopian <i>bolo</i>-based global community which he describes in the book.  Asa'pili is not a full language, but a basic vocabulary of about thirty words, which can be used to refer to cultural institutions and concepts.\n</p><p>The complete list of the basic words is as follows:\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Glyph\n</th>\n<th>Pronunciation\n</th>\n<th>Meaning\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-ibu.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of ibu\"><img alt=\"Symbol of ibu\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Bologlyph-ibu.svg/30px-Bologlyph-ibu.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Bologlyph-ibu.svg/45px-Bologlyph-ibu.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Bologlyph-ibu.svg/60px-Bologlyph-ibu.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">ibu</td>\n<td>\"individual, person\"\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bolo-glyph_bolo%27bolo_P_M.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of bolo\"><img alt=\"Symbol of bolo\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Bolo-glyph_bolo%27bolo_P_M.svg/30px-Bolo-glyph_bolo%27bolo_P_M.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Bolo-glyph_bolo%27bolo_P_M.svg/45px-Bolo-glyph_bolo%27bolo_P_M.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Bolo-glyph_bolo%27bolo_P_M.svg/60px-Bolo-glyph_bolo%27bolo_P_M.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">bolo</td>\n<td>\"community, village, tribe\" (basic autonomous social unit of 300-500 persons)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-sila.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of sila\"><img alt=\"Symbol of sila\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Bologlyph-sila.svg/30px-Bologlyph-sila.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Bologlyph-sila.svg/45px-Bologlyph-sila.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Bologlyph-sila.svg/60px-Bologlyph-sila.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">sila</td>\n<td>\"hospitality, tolerance, mutual aid\" (includes individual rights to <i>taku</i>, <i>yalu</i>, <i>gano</i>, <i>bete</i>, <i>fasi</i>, <i>nima</i>, <i>yaka</i>, and <i>nugo</i>)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-taku.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of taku\"><img alt=\"Symbol of taku\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Bologlyph-taku.svg/30px-Bologlyph-taku.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Bologlyph-taku.svg/45px-Bologlyph-taku.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Bologlyph-taku.svg/60px-Bologlyph-taku.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">taku</td>\n<td>\"personal property, secret\" (right of each person to keep a footlocker of 0.25 cubic meters for inviolable storage of personal possessions; everything else is ultimately communal)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-kana.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of kana\"><img alt=\"Symbol of kana\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ee/Bologlyph-kana.svg/30px-Bologlyph-kana.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ee/Bologlyph-kana.svg/45px-Bologlyph-kana.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ee/Bologlyph-kana.svg/60px-Bologlyph-kana.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">kana</td>\n<td>\"household, hunting party, family, gang\" (close-knit group of 15\u201330 people within a <i>bolo</i>)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-nima.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of nima\"><img alt=\"Symbol of nima\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Bologlyph-nima.svg/30px-Bologlyph-nima.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Bologlyph-nima.svg/45px-Bologlyph-nima.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Bologlyph-nima.svg/60px-Bologlyph-nima.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">nima</td>\n<td>\"way of life, tradition, culture\" (also, the right to practice and advocate for one's chosen way of life)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-kodu.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of kodu\"><img alt=\"Symbol of kodu\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Bologlyph-kodu.svg/30px-Bologlyph-kodu.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Bologlyph-kodu.svg/45px-Bologlyph-kodu.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Bologlyph-kodu.svg/60px-Bologlyph-kodu.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">kodu</td>\n<td>\"agriculture, nature, sustenance\" (predominantly local \u2014 many <i>bolo</i>s are to be self-sufficient in basic foodstuffs)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-yalu.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of yalu\"><img alt=\"Symbol of yalu\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/68/Bologlyph-yalu.svg/30px-Bologlyph-yalu.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/68/Bologlyph-yalu.svg/45px-Bologlyph-yalu.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/68/Bologlyph-yalu.svg/60px-Bologlyph-yalu.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">yalu</td>\n<td>\"food, cuisine\" (predominantly prepared in units larger than nuclear-family households from locally grown supplies)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-sibi.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of sibi\"><img alt=\"Symbol of sibi\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Bologlyph-sibi.svg/30px-Bologlyph-sibi.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Bologlyph-sibi.svg/45px-Bologlyph-sibi.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Bologlyph-sibi.svg/60px-Bologlyph-sibi.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">sibi</td>\n<td>\"craft, art, industry\" (oriented towards skilled handicraft methods, rather than mass production, with frequent personal relationships between individual makers and those who use their products)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-pali.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of pali\"><img alt=\"Symbol of pali\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Bologlyph-pali.svg/30px-Bologlyph-pali.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Bologlyph-pali.svg/45px-Bologlyph-pali.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Bologlyph-pali.svg/60px-Bologlyph-pali.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">pali</td>\n<td>\"energy, fuel\" (local self-sufficiency lessens the need for high resource consumption)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-sufu.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of suvu\"><img alt=\"Symbol of suvu\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Bologlyph-sufu.svg/30px-Bologlyph-sufu.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Bologlyph-sufu.svg/45px-Bologlyph-sufu.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Bologlyph-sufu.svg/60px-Bologlyph-sufu.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">suvu</td>\n<td>\"water, water supply, well, baths\"\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-gano.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of gano\"><img alt=\"Symbol of gano\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Bologlyph-gano.svg/30px-Bologlyph-gano.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Bologlyph-gano.svg/45px-Bologlyph-gano.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Bologlyph-gano.svg/60px-Bologlyph-gano.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">gano</td>\n<td>\"house, building, dwelling\" (isolated single-family dwellings will be replaced by less wasteful buildings for <i>kana</i>s or <i>bolo</i>s)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-bete.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of bete\"><img alt=\"Symbol of bete\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/Bologlyph-bete.svg/30px-Bologlyph-bete.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/Bologlyph-bete.svg/45px-Bologlyph-bete.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/Bologlyph-bete.svg/60px-Bologlyph-bete.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">bete</td>\n<td>\"medicine, health\"\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-nugo.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of nugo\"><img alt=\"Symbol of nugo\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/Bologlyph-nugo.svg/30px-Bologlyph-nugo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/Bologlyph-nugo.svg/45px-Bologlyph-nugo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/Bologlyph-nugo.svg/60px-Bologlyph-nugo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">nugo</td>\n<td>\"death, suicide pill\" (every <i>ibu</i> has the right to commit suicide at any time, or to request aid in committing suicide if unable to do so on their own)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-pili.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of pili\"><img alt=\"Symbol of pili\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Bologlyph-pili.svg/30px-Bologlyph-pili.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Bologlyph-pili.svg/45px-Bologlyph-pili.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Bologlyph-pili.svg/60px-Bologlyph-pili.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">pili</td>\n<td>\"communication, education, language, media\" (no centralized educational curricula or one-way mass-media)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-kene.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of kene\"><img alt=\"Symbol of kene\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/Bologlyph-kene.svg/30px-Bologlyph-kene.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/Bologlyph-kene.svg/45px-Bologlyph-kene.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/Bologlyph-kene.svg/60px-Bologlyph-kene.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">kene</td>\n<td>\"communal work\" (localized initiatives to mobilize labor to accomplish necessary public tasks)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-tega.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of tega\"><img alt=\"Symbol of tega\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Bologlyph-tega.svg/30px-Bologlyph-tega.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Bologlyph-tega.svg/45px-Bologlyph-tega.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Bologlyph-tega.svg/60px-Bologlyph-tega.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">tega</td>\n<td>\"district, town\" (loose self-governing affiliation of from ten to twenty <i>bolo</i>s)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-dala.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of dala\"><img alt=\"Symbol of dala\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Bologlyph-dala.svg/30px-Bologlyph-dala.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Bologlyph-dala.svg/45px-Bologlyph-dala.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Bologlyph-dala.svg/60px-Bologlyph-dala.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">dala</td>\n<td>\"council, assembly\" (forum for discussion and settlement of issues larger than a single <i>bolo</i>)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-dudi.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of dudi\"><img alt=\"Symbol of dudi\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/Bologlyph-dudi.svg/30px-Bologlyph-dudi.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/Bologlyph-dudi.svg/45px-Bologlyph-dudi.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/Bologlyph-dudi.svg/60px-Bologlyph-dudi.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">dudi</td>\n<td>\"foreigner, observer\" (external delegates who participate in <i>dala</i>s outside their own district or region)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-fudo.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of vudo\"><img alt=\"Symbol of vudo\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Bologlyph-fudo.svg/30px-Bologlyph-fudo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Bologlyph-fudo.svg/45px-Bologlyph-fudo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Bologlyph-fudo.svg/60px-Bologlyph-fudo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">vudo</td>\n<td>\"city, county, trading area, bioregion\" (about 400 <i>bolo</i>s)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-sumi.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of sumi\"><img alt=\"Symbol of sumi\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/Bologlyph-sumi.svg/30px-Bologlyph-sumi.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/Bologlyph-sumi.svg/45px-Bologlyph-sumi.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/Bologlyph-sumi.svg/60px-Bologlyph-sumi.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">sumi</td>\n<td>\"region, linguistic area, island\" (about twenty to thirty <i>vudo</i>s, the \"largest practical unity\")\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-asa.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of asa\"><img alt=\"Symbol of asa\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Bologlyph-asa.svg/30px-Bologlyph-asa.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Bologlyph-asa.svg/45px-Bologlyph-asa.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Bologlyph-asa.svg/60px-Bologlyph-asa.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">asa</td>\n<td>\"earth, world\"\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-buni.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of buni\"><img alt=\"Symbol of buni\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Bologlyph-buni.svg/30px-Bologlyph-buni.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Bologlyph-buni.svg/45px-Bologlyph-buni.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Bologlyph-buni.svg/60px-Bologlyph-buni.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">buni</td>\n<td>\"gift, present\" (informal exchange of goods which largely replaces commercial trade)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-mafa.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of mafa\"><img alt=\"Symbol of mafa\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Bologlyph-mafa.svg/30px-Bologlyph-mafa.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Bologlyph-mafa.svg/45px-Bologlyph-mafa.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Bologlyph-mafa.svg/60px-Bologlyph-mafa.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">mafa</td>\n<td>\"depot, warehouse\" (organized reserves of basic items in case of collective or individual need)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-feno.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of feno\"><img alt=\"Symbol of feno\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Bologlyph-feno.svg/30px-Bologlyph-feno.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Bologlyph-feno.svg/45px-Bologlyph-feno.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Bologlyph-feno.svg/60px-Bologlyph-feno.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">feno</td>\n<td>\"barter agreement, trade relation\" (more strictly reciprocal than gifts)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-sadi.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of sadi\"><img alt=\"Symbol of sadi\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Bologlyph-sadi.svg/30px-Bologlyph-sadi.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Bologlyph-sadi.svg/45px-Bologlyph-sadi.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Bologlyph-sadi.svg/60px-Bologlyph-sadi.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">sadi</td>\n<td>\"market, stock market, fair\" (commercial trade for high-value or non-local items, has a limited role in the overall economy)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-fasi.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of fasi\"><img alt=\"Symbol of fasi\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ce/Bologlyph-fasi.svg/30px-Bologlyph-fasi.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ce/Bologlyph-fasi.svg/45px-Bologlyph-fasi.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ce/Bologlyph-fasi.svg/60px-Bologlyph-fasi.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">fasi</td>\n<td>\"travel, transport, traffic, nomadism\" (the right to travel everywhere at will; however, most travel will be local by low-energy methods)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bologlyph-yaka.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Symbol of yaka\"><img alt=\"Symbol of yaka\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Bologlyph-yaka.svg/30px-Bologlyph-yaka.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Bologlyph-yaka.svg/45px-Bologlyph-yaka.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Bologlyph-yaka.svg/60px-Bologlyph-yaka.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"120\" data-file-height=\"120\" /></a></div></div></td>\n<td align=\"center\">yaka</td>\n<td>\"disagreement, war, duel\" (the right to challenge other individuals or communities to a duel or melee under specified terms)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td align=\"center\">munu</td>\n<td>\"reputation\" (more important than money in being able to cooperate productively with others)\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>All these terms (except <i>munu</i>) are accompanied by corresponding abstract glyphs,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> so that the concepts can be represented visually independently of any specific writing system.  These words can be combined into modifier-modified compounds (with the two elements separated by an apostrophe), so that <i>asa'pili</i> means \"world language\", <i>fasi'ibu</i> means \"traveler\", <i>vudo'dala</i> means \"county-level assembly\", etc.  Doubling a noun changes it into a collective or abstract noun, so that <i>bolo'bolo</i> means \"all <i>bolo</i>s, the system of <i>bolo</i>s\".\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Asa%27pili&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.lyber-eclat.net/lyber/bolo/asapili.html\">Lyber-eclat.net</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Bibliography\">Bibliography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Asa%27pili&amp;